<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engl., Veg. Erde 9 (3, 1): 274" authorityYear="1915" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Inversodicraea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Inversodicraea kamerunensis" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kamerunensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Inversodicraea kamerunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org as Vulnerable (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2017-3.RLTS.T185482A120463590.en" author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B51" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2017c. Inversodicraeakamerunensis (amended version of 2010 assessment). The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2017: e.T185482A120463590. https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2017-3.RLTS.T185482A120463590.en" title="Inversodicraeakamerunensis (amended version of 2010 assessment). The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2017: e. T 185482 A 120463590." url="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2017-3.RLTS.T185482A120463590.en" year="2017 c">Ghogue 2017c</bibRefCitation>
). It was assessed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
as Critically Endangered. The species is endemic to Cameroon and known from only the type locality; the species has not been collected since 1908. The extent of occurrence and the area of occupancy are both estimated at 4 km2 each. The main threat at this locality is dam construction on Ntem River. 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. kamerunensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="kamerunensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">I. kamerunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here reassessed and Critically Endangered status maintained. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered CRB1+2ab (ii, iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
